                            <comment id="416948" author="JIRAUSER18717" created="Fri, 7 Jun 2024 13:57:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I forgot to precise that Lustre modules are rebuilt on-target (Ubuntu 24.04, with GCC 13.2.0) using DKMS.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With Ubuntu 24.04, GCC 13.2.0 man page indicates a default behaviour change in this direction :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
 &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; NOTE:&#160; In&#160; Ubuntu 8.10 and later versions, -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2, in Ubuntu 24.04 and later versions, -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=3, is set by &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;default&lt;/span&gt;, and is activated when -O is set to 2 or higher.&#160; This enables additional compile-time and run-time
&#160;&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; checks &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; several libc functions.&#160; To disable, specify either -U_FORTIFY_SOURCE or -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=0._FORTIFY_SOURCE&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and _FORTIFY_SOURCE details can be found at :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://maskray.me/blog/2022-11-06-fortify-source&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maskray.me/blog/2022-11-06-fortify-sourcehttps://developers.redhat.com/articles/2022/09/17/gccs-new-fortification-level#1__a_new_builtin_provides_enhanced_buffer_size_detection&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What puzzles me is that looking at the disassembly code :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
0xffffffffc2de3a50 &amp;lt;lmv_fid2path&amp;gt;:&#160; &#160; &#160; nopl &#160; 0x0(%rax,%rax,1) [FTRACE NOP]
0xffffffffc2de3a55 &amp;lt;lmv_fid2path+5&amp;gt;:&#160; &#160; push &#160; %rbp
0xffffffffc2de3a56 &amp;lt;lmv_fid2path+6&amp;gt;:&#160; &#160; mov&#160; &#160; %rsp,%rbp
0xffffffffc2de3a59 &amp;lt;lmv_fid2path+9&amp;gt;:&#160; &#160; push &#160; %r15
0xffffffffc2de3a5b &amp;lt;lmv_fid2path+11&amp;gt;: &#160; push &#160; %r14
0xffffffffc2de3a5d &amp;lt;lmv_fid2path+13&amp;gt;: &#160; push &#160; %r13
0xffffffffc2de3a5f &amp;lt;lmv_fid2path+15&amp;gt;: &#160; mov&#160; &#160; %esi,%r13d
0xffffffffc2de3a62 &amp;lt;lmv_fid2path+18&amp;gt;: &#160; push &#160; %r12
0xffffffffc2de3a64 &amp;lt;lmv_fid2path+20&amp;gt;: &#160; push &#160; %r10
0xffffffffc2de3a66 &amp;lt;lmv_fid2path+22&amp;gt;: &#160; push &#160; %rbx
0xffffffffc2de3a67 &amp;lt;lmv_fid2path+23&amp;gt;: &#160; sub&#160; &#160; $0x50,%rsp
0xffffffffc2de3a6b &amp;lt;lmv_fid2path+27&amp;gt;: &#160; mov&#160; &#160; %rdx,-0x50(%rbp)
0xffffffffc2de3a6f &amp;lt;lmv_fid2path+31&amp;gt;: &#160; mov&#160; &#160; %rcx,-0x48(%rbp)
0xffffffffc2de3a73 &amp;lt;lmv_fid2path+35&amp;gt;: &#160; mov&#160; &#160; %gs:0x28,%rax
